6967L6.21967 11.7197L7.28033 12.7803L11.5303 8.53033L10.4697 7.46967Z"></path><path stroke="currentColor" d="M1.75 8H11" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" class="origin-left transition-all duration-200 opacity-0 motion-safe:-translate-x-1 group-hover:translate-x-0 group-hover:opacity-100"></path></svg></a></div><h2>Teaching</h2>
<ul>
<li>Fall 2019: Computational Fabrication (<a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://courses.cs.washington.edu/courses/cse556/19au/" class="animated-underline custom-link text-primary-700 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus:outline-none focus-visible:rounded focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 border-dark border-b border-dotted hover:border-black/0">CSE 556</a>)</li>
<li>Spring 2019: Reseach Seminar: Geometry Processing (<a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://homes.cs.washington.edu/~adriana/GeoProc/index.html" class="animated-underline custom-link text-primary-700 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus:outline-none focus-visible:rounded focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 border-dark border-b border-dotted hover:border-black/0">CSE 590-K</a>)</li>
<li>Winter 2019: Special Topics in Computational Fabrication (<a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://courses.cs.washington.edu/courses/cse599j1/19wi/" class="animated-underline custom-link text-primary-700 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus:outline-none focus-visible:rounded focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 border-dark border-b border-dotted hover:border-black/0">CSE 599-J1</a>)</li>
<li>Fall 2018: Computational Fabrication (<a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://courses.cs.washington.edu/courses/cse556/18au/" class="animated-underline custom-link text-primary-700 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus:outline-none focus-visible:rounded focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 border-dark border-b border-dotted hover:border-black/0">CSE 556</a>)</li>
</ul>
<h2>Bio</h2>
<p>I grew up in Brazil, where I earned a Bachelor&#x27;s degree in Electronics Engineering from <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.impa.br/" class="animated-underline custom-link text-primary-700 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus:outline-none focus-visible:rounded focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 border-dark border-b border-dotted hover:border-black/0">UFRJ</a> and a Master&#x27;s in Mathematics from <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.impa.br/" class="animated-underline custom-link text-primary-700 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus:outline-none focus-visible:rounded focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 border-dark border-b border-dotted hover:border-black/0">IMPA</a>. I completed my Ph.D. in Computer Science at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.csail.mit.edu/" class="animated-underline custom-link text-primary-700 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus:outline-none focus-visible:rounded focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 border-dark border-b border-dotted hover:border-black/0">MIT</a> in 2018. After that, I spent several wonderful years at the <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.cs.washington.edu/" class="animated-underline custom-link text-primary-700 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus:outline-none focus-visible:rounded focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 border-dark border-b border-dotted hover:border-black/0">University of Washington</a>, where I served as an Assistant Professor of Computer Science and was later promoted to Associate Professor with tenure. I joined <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://brown.edu" class="animated-underline custom-link text-primary-700 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus:outline-none focus-visible:rounded focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 border-dark border-b border-dotted hover:border-black/0">Brown University</a> in 2025.</p></div></di